<DOC sysid="rbmt-3" docid="denik.cz/2012/12/01/62159" genre="news" origlang="cs">
<h1>
<seg id="1">Š imon Ornest: In our concerts we want to accumulate positive energy</seg>
</h1>
<p>
<seg id="2">It is said that in little less than one month the end of the world is going to come: what does he think about it?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3">It is only one of between so many other alarmist news to which it likes seizing us.</seg>
<seg id="4">The group of musician The Tap Tap us likes doing rather pranks on this and we like saying that we are the only group of music of the world that manages to assemble enough positive energy to postpone the end of the world or to avoid it.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5">Also, in December you organize a really original project: three concerts against the end of the world.</seg>
<seg id="6">Can it be explained to our readership?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="7">It is a question of a state charitable act that we take gliding for two years.</seg>
<seg id="8">We decide to make use of the potential of marketing that has the end of the Mayan calendar enunciated for December 21 at 11:10 a.m.</seg>
<seg id="9">The previous day, December 20 at 21 a.m., we will organize 3 simultaneous concerts in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.</seg>
<seg id="10">They will end approximately at the same time when it finishes the Mayan calendar in the island Kiribati, in the Pacific Ocean, 12 hours ahead of our hourly area.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="11">To whom did this idea occur?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="12">Initially it was my idea, later we were forging the project all together with our designer Honza Augusta.</seg>
<seg id="13">In addition to wanting to assemble enough positive energy and avoid the end of the world, also we want to reflect, together with the society, on the state in which we will leave the world to our children.</seg>
<seg id="14">On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar also we have created the only articles collection: boots, T-shirts, bags and original turnkeys against the end of the world that can be acquired in www.e-tap.cz, another way of supporting us.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="15">The group The Tap Tap, together with other interpreters, also sang the called anthem against the end of the world, which goes for title "End of the world, cancelled".</seg>
<seg id="16">At present it is very popular in YouTube: will it be possible to hear in the charitable concerts?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="17">Skylight that yes, and it will be just last, well, whenever everything goes out well and the world is not finished...</seg>
<seg id="18">All the interpreters will sing it at the same time in three concerts.</seg>
<seg id="19">The anthems will be connected between themselves simultaneously thanks to the live special transmission in the Czech Television.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="20">Tomá Hanák has written the letter of this song and Jesus's protagonist plays the role in the video, where also he sings Xindl X...</seg>
<seg id="21">How did this collaboration arise?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="22">We work jointly even with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, apart from organizing many charitable acts and concerts...</seg>
<seg id="23">We put all our determination in taking part in this project.</seg>
<seg id="24">It has been demonstrated that most of them are interested in and it entertains them to work with us.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="25">To what will be assined the money collected in the concerts against the end of the world?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="26">To equipment for the educational center without barriers Studeo, which we take to term in its sixth consecutive year with the civil association Tap in Jedličkův ústav.</seg>
<seg id="27">The pupils of the school of Jedličkův ústav receive regularly the teachers' visit with those who realize entertaining and interesting activities.</seg>
<seg id="28">The pupils have not sufficient economic means to pay away from the teachers and we do an efuerzo to make it possible.</seg>
<seg id="29">In the frame of the ending of the works in Jedličkův ústav, there will exist an independent building to which we will move with this project.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="30">In every concert several groups and interpreters act.</seg>
<seg id="31">What are the selection criteria?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="32">We try to prepare a program that is attractive for all the generations, including the children.</seg>
<seg id="33">For example, in Prague they will operate Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Bárta, The Tap Tap, Marián Bango and Jiří Such ý.</seg>
<seg id="34">To obtain more detailed information, you can consult www.kpks.cz.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="35">Do you intend for any other "spectacular action" similar in the future?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="36">In May we will operate for the first time in the festival Pražské arum lily, so here of course we will prepare an attractive program with interesting guests.</seg>
<seg id="37">Also we would like to touch the next year me in Bohemian National Entrance hall of New York and, personally, making use that we are in the United States, I would like completing it with performances in Washington and in Chicago.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="38">Your plans abroad are not precisely minimalistas, till now you have acted for example in Madrid, Brussels, London or Moscow.</seg>
<seg id="39">The Tap Tap is, nevertheless, a group formed by persons with disability.</seg>
<seg id="40">How is the logistics and the organization of these trips?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="41">It is not so difficult how it can seem at first sight.</seg>
<seg id="42">There are five members in electrical wheelchair, the chairs must travel in the compartment for baggage and also we take a lot of weight, the boxes with the instruments...</seg>
<seg id="43">Nevertheless, till now we have managed them well. THAT ONE and British Airways were prepared perfectly, thing that it does not stop surprising me.</seg>
<seg id="44">Even in Moscow, from which we have returned not long ago, it went out quite without problems.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="45">Thanks to the exits abroad you can compare the different attitudes of the society towards the disabled ones and other aspects.</seg>
<seg id="46">What have you met till now?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="47">In Madrid, Luxembourg, London and other cities, everything works better than here; in Russia we have been witnesses of that, in the East, a lot of way stays for covering.</seg>
<seg id="48">In contrast to Prague, Moscow is full of barriers, there it continues and it is not frequent that a person displeases alone for the center of the city in an electrical wheelchair.</seg>
<seg id="49">A little so current as it is, for example, to give preference to someone in wheelchair in elevator, there it it is not.</seg>
<seg id="50">Fortunately, there has been created a civil association that strengthens for tematizar the problems of the persons with disability.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="51">In what aspects must we take example of more anticipated countries?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="52">There are many aspects in which we go behind...</seg>
<seg id="53">But it is important to mention that the improving and the progress of the situation always depends on the persons whom it affects straight.</seg>
<seg id="54">In London and in Madrid it is very normal that the people with a serious disability move for its account in public and could go to the service, to the museum, where he wants...</seg>
<seg id="55">But it is not very common that a big number of persons with disability takes part in the social life of active form, in this aspect, with The Tap Tap: we go a little ahead!</seg>
<seg id="56">A respectful society or without barriers it is a thing, but when there comes the moment in which there arise eminent sportsmen, artists, actors, politicians or lawyers, it will begin changing everything really.</seg>
<seg id="57">Till now, there are isolated cases of persons who have a big willpower.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="58">The group The Tap Tap is at present very popular, but if we look a few years behind: what led you to forming the group in 1998?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="59">I entered like educator Jedličkův ústav, where many young people had around me that they wanted to devote themselves to something.</seg>
<seg id="60">And since I am musical, I touch, between others, the saxophone, founded a group amateur with a coworker.</seg>
<seg id="61">And with the time, as our moderator Láďa Angelovič says, it us went away a little of the hands (laughs).</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="62">Nevertheless, the popularity did not come until the latter years: or am I wrong?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="63">It is true that we were helped enough by the fact of tuning in to famous singers and also of working actively to promote the group.</seg>
<seg id="64">We come to the conclusion that the work that is not seen, is as if it did not exist.</seg>
<seg id="65">Thanks to the helps of the European Union, we can allow ourselves also professorship of quality, equipment, etc.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="66">Did you have intention of coming that far with The Tap Tap?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="67">From the beginning I saw the potential that existed, that it is possible to do something otherwise.</seg>
<seg id="68">The world of the spectacle is full of things that look like some to others.</seg>
<seg id="69">It is logical, in its way, everything new it takes refuge carefully and takes a lot of time in be accepting.</seg>
<seg id="70">There are few extraordinary things, but I dare to say that The Tap Tap is one of them.</seg>
<seg id="71">The impression of someone who sees us for the first time is clearly the compassion, it is a natural reaction...</seg>
<seg id="72">But the compassion is completely superfluous because the persons with disability are not godforsaken beings who suffer and of that we should have compassion.</seg>
<seg id="73">There are the people who is capable of living through a full life and of developing, with the condition, of course, of which he has the necessary means.</seg>
<seg id="74">I always say that if something goes out well for persons with disability, then, it is not an only one advance for them, but for the whole society.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="75">Did it help the fact that you are a demanding chief, as many people describe him?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="76">If we want to do a quality work, we have to be rigorous in many aspects and demand certain discipline.</seg>
<seg id="77">I believe that it is completely normal.</seg>
<seg id="78">Some persons come with a romantic vision and with the head in the clouds and when it find out that have to come two days to test, go to the preparatory test and spend a lot of time traveling and in concerts, the initial euphoria leaves them quickly.</seg>
<seg id="79">But this way it is how it works everywhere, in every group that wants to work and obtain something.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="80">At present the group The Tap Tap has twenty members.</seg>
<seg id="81">How many of them were already in the beginnings of the year 1998?</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="82">The only one: Láďa Angelovič.</seg>
<seg id="83">We are an open group, the people enter and go out, it is not possible to avoid.</seg>
<seg id="84">The one who has will and desire will always find the open doors</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="85">It will be the day before the awaited end of the world, Thursday, the 20.12.2012th at 21 a.m.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="86">It will take place in Incheba Arena of Prague, in Fléda de Brno and in Plynojem in Ostrava and there will take part 12 groups and other musicians of the Czech Republic</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="87">Three cities will get connected at the end of the party across videoconference to sing jointly the song of the group The Tap Tap "End of the world, cancelled"</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="88">The target of the concert is to assemble the necessary resources to finance multifunctional equipment of the educational center without barriers STUDEO in Jedličkův ústav of Prague, which cost amounts to 25 million Czech crowns.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="89">The entry to the concert costs 400 CZK and the children up to 12 years have free entry in the put anticipated in Bohemiaticket</seg>
</p>
</doc>
<DOC sysid="rbmt-3" docid="idnes.cz/2012/12/01/494025" genre="news" origlang="cs">
<h1>
<seg id="1">Poland and the cosmos.</seg>
</h1>
<p>
<seg id="2">In the ministers' meeting of the countries of the celebrated European Spatial Agency last week Poland was accepted like twelfth member of THAT ONE. It is the second member country of THAT ONE of the ancient East Europe block, after the Czech Republic, which turned into full member on November 12, 2008).</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="3">Poland initiated an intense collaboration with THAT ONE in the year 1994 and during the later years it took part in the project commission of the agency.</seg>
<seg id="4">Nevertheless, the way of Poland towards the cosmos started very much earlier.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="5">The Polish enthusiasts were already devoting themselves to the flights to the space before the Second World war, although not always its work was understood.</seg>
<seg id="6">I remember, for example, the conference of A. Š ternfeld in the astronomical observatory of Warsaw in which, on December 6, 1933, it presented its ideas on the pioneering study "Introduction to the cosmonáutica".</seg>
<seg id="7">The ideas of the young engineer (born 1905) left the indifferent assistants and, years later, Š ternfeld he remembered that Dr. Jan Gadomski had been the only one that had showed interest in its work.</seg>
<seg id="8">In the year 1934 Š ternfeld Robert Esnault-Pelterie and André Louis Hirsch obtained in France the award for its "Introduction to the cosmonáutica".</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="9">The doctor Jan Gadomski (1899 - 1966), mentioned previously, turned later into a big promoter of the astronomy and of the cosmonáutica.</seg>
<seg id="10">He published hundreds of articles in Polish magazines and wrote a series of books dedicated to this scientific discipline.</seg>
<seg id="11">Gadomski turned into a promoter of the cosmonáutica, it was known in the whole world and its contribution to the science turned out to be rewarded when its name put itself to one of the craters of the secret face of the moon.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="12">Already in the year 1925 there was constructed in Poland a dresina that was going to be provided with a rockets engine.</seg>
<seg id="13">Regrettably, is not known who the author of the proposal was and neither the destalles of the project are known.</seg>
<seg id="14">It is not clear if the rocket was going to be used for the starter of the dresina or for its braking.</seg>
<seg id="15">The information about this dresina limits itself to the collection in the press of the epoch.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="16">From the year 1933 the Polish artillery began devoting itself to the missiles.</seg>
<seg id="17">The investigation was financed by Komórka Techniki Uzbrojenia in collaboration with the prof. Mieczyslawem Wolfkem and prof. Gustawem Mokrzyckiegim.</seg>
<seg id="18">From the preserved material, it makes clear to him that the investigation came to the stadium of the practical tests.</seg>
<seg id="19">Nevertheless, with the arrival of the German troops, the investigation was interrupted.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="20">In the year 1937 there appeared in the specializing press the prototype of a missile of photoelectric fighter designed by the engineer Rohoziński and the study was published the following year "Rakieta - torpeda powietrzna i rakietobomba lotnicza", of author Leliwa-Krzywoblocki.</seg>
<seg id="21">Both projects were destined for the military use of the engines for missiles.</seg>
<seg id="22">Shortly before the war, the Committee provisional scientific adviser (Tymczasowy Komitet Doradczo-Naukowy) was taking charge of all the projects of skills of missiles for military use and was coordinating all the works.</seg>
<seg id="23">The committee was founded in 1937, but after two years of activity, he turned out to be interrupted in the beginning of the war.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="24">Other studies dedicated to the cosmonáutica appeared in the Polish press after the war thanks to the work of the Polish Society of Astronautics (Polskie Towarzystwo Astronautyczne).</seg>
<seg id="25">In the edition of November, 1954 of the magazine Problemy one refers for the first time to the society with four very extensive articles dedicated to the astronautics.</seg>
<seg id="26">In one of them, of the prof. M. Subotowicze, there was proposed the creation of a society who would devote herself to the cosmonáutica.</seg>
<seg id="27">In this epoch artificial satellites projects had already been started and it was obvious that the cosmic investigation was a discipline with future perspectives.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="28">From the beginning of 1956 the Polish Society of Astronautics (PTA) was aspiring to be part of the International Federation of Astronautics (founded in 1951) and in autumn of the same year the PTA turned into full member.</seg>
<seg id="29">The following year the first president of the PTA, Kazimierz Zarankiewicz (1902 - 1959), happened to be the vice-president of the International Federation of Astronautics.</seg>
<seg id="30">It redeemed this charge up to its death in 1959.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="31">From 1956, the PTA informed in a significant way in the development of the rocket probe RM (Rakieta Meteorologiczna), which was a success and turned into the first Polish rocket in which scientific investigation was carried out.</seg>
<seg id="32">The first type RM-1 was finished in 1957 and he was thrown for the first time on October 10, 1958.</seg>
<seg id="33">The rocket had a 1.800 meters climax, approximately 80 cm long and was not coming to weight of 5 kg.</seg>
<seg id="34">Later, one stopped constructing the version RM-1A and in summer 1959 there began the air tests of the rockets RM-2 of two stages in the Błędów desert.</seg>
<seg id="35">The rocket was measuring 1,4 meters and was weighing approximately 11,5 kg.</seg>
<seg id="36">Another type of rocket in development was going to be an object of real scientific study. The rocket RM-34 was going to have a 14,5 km climax and its mission would be to control the height wind.</seg>
<seg id="37">Nevertheless, in 1962 the works were suspended.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="38">The successor of the first rockets of the type RM was the rocket Meteor-1, which was constructed during the year 1962 and 1965.</seg>
<seg id="39">It was designed like rocket of two stages, with a 510 cm entire length and an initial weight of 32,5 kg.</seg>
<seg id="40">There developed three types (called Meteor-1A,-1B and-1C), which were differing between themselves for the space available for the scientific devices.</seg>
<seg id="41">In the rocket Meteor-1A the space available for the volume was 0,4 liters, in the 0,34 liters Meteor-1B and in the Meteor-1C of 0,62 liters.</seg>
<seg id="42">The maximum climax in three types was 37 km.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="43">Between the year 1965 and 1968 there developed in the Air Institute the rocket Meteor-2, which first air tests began in October, 1970.</seg>
<seg id="44">The rocket Meteor-2 had 380 kg initial weight and it was capable of taking 10 kg useful weight up to 60 km high.</seg>
<seg id="45">Later there was constructed the version Meteor-2H and Meteor-3.</seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id="46">It is necessary to mention also the entry of Poland in the COSPAR (Committee for Space Research) in the year 1960 and the formation of the national committee of COSPAR two years later.</seg>
<seg id="47">In the frame of the program Interkosmos, Poland it joined the investigation of the cosmic space on Soviet artificial satellites and, in the year 1978, pilot Polish Miroslaw Hermaszewski turned into the second intercosmonaut after Vladimír Remek.</seg>
</p>
</doc>
<DOC sysid="rbmt-3" docid="idnes.cz/2012/12/01/494056" genre="news" origlang="cs">
<h1>
<seg id="1">The suspension of the law on social works is not the solution.</seg>
</h1>
<p>
<seg id="2">Last week the constitutional court suspended the law traabajos social.</seg>
<seg id="3">The resolution woke up a heated discussion in the society.</seg>
<seg id="4">Certainly it will be interesting to examine the existing problems from a wider point of view.</seg>
